<br>
I already have a 65 Bard and 65 Cleric and was thinking of getting a 3rd account to stick another bot on to 3-box.   Main areas of consideration for the trio in order of importance to me:<br>
<br>
1. Solo XP-ing.  I play a lot of off-peak hours and the ability to 3-box some XP camps alone would be welcome.<br>
<br>
2. XP-ing with others.  Ease of adding random guildmates who log on and doing something (Normal LDoN comes to mind).<br>
<br>
3. Harder XP-ing with others.  Having 2 out of 3 or all 3 of my chars able to contribute to a group.  For harder encounters where 2-boxing is a better idea than 3-boxing (such as GoD trials or LDoN hard), having the flexibility to choose between bard + (cleric or X).  For example, if healing is covered by a cleric buddy, choose X.  If no healer then choose my cleric.  My bard will always be one of the chars I play.<br>
<br>
For these types of groups, I breakdown the roles needed as tanking, healing, CC, slow, DPS.  Probably taking all 3 roles such as tanking, healing, CC will be too overwhelming and group performance will suffer too much.  So maybe a DPS class is the way to go for this 3rd point.<br>
<br>
My main concern with this 3rd point is to have enough of the roles covered such that it makes finding filler classes for the group less troublesome.  I don't want to be able to cover all roles with my trio as I'm sure 3-boxing in this environment will impact the groups performance.  And that, to me, is important above all. (Plus I think it's impossible to cover all 3 roles given that I already have a bard and cleric).  It may be possible with a trinity trio, ie. War, Cleric, Enc, but that is not an option as I don't want to drop my bard.<br>
<br>
I'm satisfied if I'm left with one of the following situations:<br>
&quot;All I need is a tank and we're good to go&quot;<br>
&quot;All I need is a slower and we're good to go&quot;<br>
&quot;All I need is some DPS and we're good to go&quot;.<br>
<br>
4. Raids.  Being useful on a raid is a plus.  However, I'm intimidated by having to get the new char all PoP flags again (as I just finished finished off my cleric's elemental access).  So I'm just throwing this point out there to get some feedback.  It's really at the bottom of my list as I'm not looking forward to reflagging or using up some of my guild's precious 15% flag allocation.<br>
<br>
Links to my magelos are included in my sig if it adds an insight.<br>
<br>
