<br>
Wizard<br>
Magician<br>
Necro<br>
Druid<br>
Beastlord?<br>
<br>
Wizard and Magician are pretty straight forward.  Snare and evac being the main appeals of the wizard class as my 3rd box.  While Magician being nice for those times when things get a bit hectic and all I have to do is sic the pet on the mob.<br>
<br>
Necro......seems like they're usually quite busy in an xp group.  Or maybe that's just my perception.  Would doing the HP/Mana taps, pet attack and DoTing be a little too much work?<br>
<br>
Druid......a little redundancy in healing.  Snare and evac are very nice.  I figure DoTs would help in situations where my bard would be forced to tank (as far as holding aggro is concerned).  Decent enough nukes.<br>
<br>
Beastlord.....pet attack for those times when its hectic.  Slightly better slow (the fact that you dont need to refresh our slow song every min is appealing).  On a 65 BST, how much of its DPS is from meeleeing vs the warder?  Will I be losing 50% of the class' DPS if I'm usually just sending the pet in most of the time?  How about aggro?  Will this lesser equipped BST pull aggro more from my Elemental equipped bard (I'll definitely want the  bard tanking if possible).<br>
<br>
Based on all of these, how would you all rank these 5 classes as a 3rd box?  Thanks for all the feedback and comments so far.  It's all very appreciated. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140777" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Psynic - L65 Wood Elf Maestro</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
