<br>
I often 3box my Bard/Druid/Beastlord combo and I see it as similar to yours.  My bard is always the MT (400ish AAs) and I have no problems holding aggro as long as I sing at least 2 of the dot songs.  I had my bard and druid before I added the beast 3rd toon.  I considered a wizard, but already had the transportation, snares, and evacs in the druid, so I decided on the bst.  His pet adds nice DPS, I use his slow at times on harder mobs (but not always, ours is generally good enough and I don't like the mobs to aggro my bst).<br>
<br>
I kind of digressed in telling you about my 3box but it was mainly to point out that I've been there and done that.  I wanted to reinforce (at least for me), how much I love having the instant evac.  I like to do things with just my 3 toons that I haven't done before.  Its nice to go in and try something, find out that maybe my strategy needs to be tweaked, and have the ability to evac out (using druid instant evac AA) and then move in and try again.  I'm not sure how important that will be to you as you can just rez and start over, but for me its very handy.  I find that I'm much more willing, even eager, to go try something just to see if I can do it, knowing that I can bail if the situation turns sour. For you, a wizard adds this ability along with awesome DPS to your mini group.  The mage is certainly a stong choice for you (I sometimes wonder if I shouldn't have done a mage over my bst) if you're willing to give up on the snare/evac.<br>
<br>
